<div><strong>Admission Requirements:</strong></div>
<ul>
<li>A BYU-Idaho Cumulative GPA of 3.5 based on at least one 12 credit semester, is required at the time of application <span style="text-decoration: underline;">and</span> selections</li>
<li>The highest grade entered in a course which has been retaken will be used for Associate Degree Selections. Original and retake grades will no longer be averaged.</li>
<li>Complete at least one 12-credit semester (university or college)</li>
<li>Complete BIO 264 and BIO 265 with a grade of "B" or higher (B- and below do not qualify)</li>
<li><a href="Documents/nursing/nursing/ASN/Application/Kaplan Pre-Admission Ltr 11-2012.pdf">Kaplan Pre-Admission Test</a>: to be taken in the testing center berfore application is submitted <strong> </strong></li>
<li>Criminal Background Check</li>
<li>Specific Physical and Mental Requirements</li>
<li><strong>Unlike other BYU-Idaho students</strong>, students admitted to the Nursing Program must complete course work in 4 consecutive semesters once admitted to the ASN Program. This is not optional. It is the student's responsibility to ensure matriculation without interruption.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Associate Degree Special Program Requirements. </strong> <strong>In addition to the Admission Requirements, students </strong><strong><em>admitted to the program</em></strong><strong> are required to submit the following:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Specified Health Exam</li>
<li>Tuberculosis screening (required annually)</li>
<li>Immunization documentation
<ul>
<li>Hospitals require students have specific immunizations, including an annual Flu vaccine.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>CPR training
<ul>
<li><strong>American Heart Association Health Provider</strong> <span style="text-decoration: underline;">only </span>is accepted<span style="text-decoration: underline;">.</span></li>
<li>Any other certification will be denied and candidate will be required to take the specified course.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Malpractice Insurance: Provided and paid for by the University</li>
<li>Liability Release</li>
<li>Transportation: you must make your own arrangements</li>
</ul>
